title: Install Iosevka-Term Font on Ubuntu
tags: @zettel _method
roam-id: 92f66e28-3eed-4e25-9595-9bb276758281
type: text/markdown

- go to <https://www.nerdfonts.com/font-downloads>
- search "iosevkaterm"
- download the font
- extract the archive
- `mkdir iosevkaterm`
- put all `.ttf` files into `iosevkaterm` folder
- `mv iosevka-term-ttf ~/.local/share/fonts/`
- update font cache `fc-cache -fv ~/.local/share/fonts`
- you can list newly installed iosevka font with `fc-list | grep iosevka`
